content:
I cannot get xx and yy to equal each other, and I'm not sure why. I have confirmed that Matlab is producing `xTot` that is equivalent to when I calculate the sum by hand on my calculator. In addition, as I've written the code, I am sure the complex amplitudes being used for each part of the problem are consistent. What am I overlooking?

Plot:


Code:
```
c1 = 2*exp(2*1j);
c2 = exp(1.5*1j);
c3 = 1.5*exp(-1*1j);
c4 = 3;
c5 = 1.2*exp(-1.2*1j);

hz = 200;
fs = 100;
tstart = 0;
tend = 1;

xx1 = onecos(c1, hz, fs, tstart, tend);
xx2 = onecos(c2 , hz, fs, tstart, tend);
xx3 = onecos(c3, hz, fs, tstart, tend);
xx4 = onecos(c4, hz, fs, tstart, tend);
xx5 = onecos(c5, hz, fs, tstart, tend);

xx = xx1 + xx2 + xx3 + xx4 + xx5;

totX = c1 + c2 + c3 + c4 + c5;

yy = onecos(totX, hz, fs, tstart, tend);

isequal(xx, yy)

ts = 0:1/fs:1;

plot(ts, xx, 'b-');
hold on;
plot(ts, yy, 'c-');
```
